The **tuba** can easily match or exceed the volume of a horn playing *ff* in the small second group (around B♭3–C4), especially in the lower register. While a trombone (B) might also be loud, it typically lacks the tuba’s sheer power and mid-range projection in this range. The flute (A) and clarinet (C) are far less voluminous in comparison.
